Impact of gynecological cancers on health-related quality of life: historical 
context, measurement instruments, and current knowledge.

Gil-Ibanez B(#)(1)(2), Davies-Oliveira J(#)(3)(4), Lopez G(5)(2), Díaz-Feijoo 
B(6), Tejerizo-Garcia A(5)(2), Sehouli J(7).

Author information:
(1)Gynecologic Oncology and Minimally Invasive Surgery Unit, Gynecology and 
Obstetrics Department, Hospital Universitario 12 de Octubre, Madrid, Spain 
blancalabacin@hotmail.com.
(2)i+12 Research Institute, Hospital Universitario 12 de Octubre, Madrid, Spain.
(3)Division of Cancer Sciences, The University of Manchester, Manchester, UK.
(4)Department of Obstetrics and Gynaecology, St Mary's Hospital, Manchester 
University NHS Foundation Trust, Manchester Academic Health Science Centre, 
Manchester, UK.
(5)Gynecologic Oncology and Minimally Invasive Surgery Unit, Gynecology and 
Obstetrics Department, Hospital Universitario 12 de Octubre, Madrid, Spain.
(6)Institute Clinic of Gynecology, Obstetrics and Neonatology, Hospital Clinic 
de Barcelona, Institutd'Investigacions Biomèdiques August Pi I Sunyer (IDIBAPS), 
